yle="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We facilitate financial education employee volunteering opportunities to make financial education real and relevant to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> young </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">people’s lives, and to help </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">pupils link learning in the classroom with life outside. Appropriate inputs from private sector industry experts can make a real impact on outcomes for students and can add significant social capital to disadvantaged young peopl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e, particularly in relation to their aspirations around work</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, career choices</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and future lifestyle.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">iii.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Crucially, as an independent charity with financial education expertise, we provide an essential quality assurance role in ensuring that information </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> resources</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> used by teachers and students are impartial and free from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">branding</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. We also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ensure supporters’ employees are adequately prepared for their volunteering experiences so the best possible outcomes are achieved for students. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">pfeg</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> also f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">acilitate</spa